This paper discusses regularization techniques for reinforcement learning (RL) agents, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also focuses on the injection of noise into the learned function, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. Additionally, the paper discusses the low-data regime encountered early on in training RL agents, which is relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
